DataElement.preferredName: Prior Monoclonal Antibody Administered Last Date
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The date of last administration for the prior use of an antibody produced by a clone or genetically homogenous fast-growing cells, i.e., hybridoma. Hybridoma cells are cloned to establish cell lines producing a specific antibody that is chemically and immunologically homogeneous and are widely used in cancer detection, diagnosis, and treatment.
